FBIS3-38793 "drweu026_p_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 GREECE Papandreou U.S. Trip Not Tied With Macedonia NC0702140194 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 1230 GMT 7 Feb 94 NC0702140194 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Language: Greek Article Type:BFN [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today said that Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou will visit the United States on 22 April, as announced on Saturday [5 February] by the responsible departments of the two countries. Asked whether Papandreou's trip will be affected by Washington's recognition of Skopje, the spokesman said: The government's policy is to convince the international factions that a solution will be found when Kiro Gligorov bends his intransigence. So, the prime minister's trip will take place as announced.
